\par 2.2\tab CATEGORY 2: USERS
\par \tab 
\par \tab #guAdmin
\par \tab #guMember
\par \tab #guGuest
\par 
\par \tab The user tag should be associated with  a <div> element immediately 
\par \tab inside the #gallery tag. There is only one user tag per document-view.
\par 
\par \tab These three classes are to allow different views to users with different 
\par \tab levels of access to a particular gallery.
\par 
\par \tab Most theme implementations should not need to use these tags; 
\par \tab please avoid using them as much as possible. Even in themes where it 
\par \tab is used in, it will not be defined directly but should be used to specify 
\par \tab styles for nested classes. 
\par 
\par \tab  For example, the  following CSS code would make hyperlinks black 
\par \tab for the Admin but blue for everyone else.
\par 
\par \tab \tab A \{ color:blue \}
\par \tab \tab #guAdmin A \{ color:black \}
