\par \tab In the templates, category 5 Items can be associated with most tags.
\par \tab Common ones are <div>, <p>, <img>, form elements, and so forth.
\par \tab 
\par \tab Generally speaking, Items are discrete elements that do not contain
\par \tab other elements within them. This rule can be broken, but it's best to
\par \tab avoid doing so when possible. In any case, Items must be children of
\par \tab either Sections or Boxes and definately shouldn't contain anything but
\par \tab other Items (or preferably, <spans>) inside themselves.
\par \tab 
\par \tab Likewise, Item classes should refer to boes and sections. Items tend 
\par \tab to be the most generic classes, and a class like giTitle will have many
\par \tab different context-sensitive styles.
\par \tab 
\par \tab Defaults should be declared in the same style used for Box defaults.
