\par \tab For each of the bottom three categories of organization there is a 
\par \tab "Spacer" element. The intent of this is to be a more flexible alternative
\par \tab to <BR> when using relative layout flows. In a template, a spacer 
\par \tab element is defined exactly like this:
\par 
\par \tab \tab <div class="gbSpacer">&nbsp;</div>
\par 
\par \tab Most themes will work with the following definition:
